    <description>Another game of the great La Bat-Series created by &amp;quot;The old guys&amp;quot; of Marshal Enterprise : &amp;#10;FRIEDLAND 1807 and the Siege of Danzig&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Two games in one package to decide the fate of Prussia and Poland.&amp;#10;5 maps, 5 full color diecut countersheets, 2 informational countersheets, allocation tables, increment charts and a full CD of historical opinions, rules and game aides. Fight on the field of honor or dig your way to the city walls, what is your fate?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;The La Bataille game series are games simulating grand tactical Napoleonic combat. The games are based on historical battles, have detailed Orders of Battles, and can range from small (the space of a coffee table) to &amp;quot;monster game&amp;quot; size (4 or more full maps.) They use the battalion as the primary unit size and 125 yards per hexagon. Units are measured in steps, each step being 100 infantry, 50 cavalry or 1 gun.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;--BGG Series Description&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Produced in a limited quantity of just 400.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Standard scale is:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     scale = 100 m/hex; &amp;#10;     time = 20 min/GT; &amp;#10;     strength = 50-100 men/SP (Regimental/Brigade Size)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
